#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.128"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.128:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.128:0.2"
msgid "13. Kusināravagga "
msgstr "13. Kusināra "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.128:0.3"
msgid "128. Kaṭuviyasutta "
msgstr "128. Bitter "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.280, sc1
msgctxt "an3.128:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ viharati isipatane migadāye. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.128:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya bārāṇasiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Benares for alms. "

#. VAR: goyogapilakkhasmiṃ → goyogamilakkhasmiṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
#. VAR: caramāno → caramānaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.128:1.3"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā goyogapilakkhasmiṃ piṇḍāya caramāno aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ rittassādaṃ bāhirassādaṃ muṭṭhassatiṃ asampajānaṃ asamāhitaṃ vibbhantacittaṃ pākatindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "While the Buddha was walking for alms near the cow-hitching place at the wavy leaf fig, he saw a disgruntled monk who was looking for pleasure in external things, unmindful, without situational awareness or immersion, with straying mind and undisciplined faculties. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.128:1.4"
msgid "Disvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said to him, "

#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu → bhikkhu bhikkhu mā kho tvaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.128:2.1"
msgid "“Mā kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, attānaṃ kaṭuviyamakāsi. "
msgstr "“Monk, don’t be bitter. "

#. VAR: āmagandhena → āmagandhe (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: nānvāssavissantīti → nānvassavissanti (pts1) | nānubandhissanti (mr)
msgctxt "an3.128:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ vata, bhikkhu, kaṭuviyakataṃ attānaṃ āmagandhena avassutaṃ makkhikā nānupatissanti nānvāssavissantīti, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti. "
msgstr "If you’re bitter, corrupted by the stench of rotting flesh, flies will, without a doubt, plague and infest you.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.128:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu bhagavatā iminā ovādena ovadito saṃvegamāpādi. "
msgstr "Hearing this advice of the Buddha, that monk was struck with a sense of urgency. "

msgctxt "an3.128:2.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, after the meal, on his return from alms-round, the Buddha told the mendicants what had happened. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.128:3.1"
msgid "“Idhāhaṃ, bhikkhave, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya bārāṇasiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.128:3.2"
msgid "Addasaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhave, goyogapilakkhasmiṃ piṇḍāya caramāno aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ rittassādaṃ bāhirassādaṃ muṭṭhassatiṃ asampajānaṃ asamāhitaṃ vibbhantacittaṃ pākatindriyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.128:3.3"
msgid "Disvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.128:4.1"
msgid "‘Mā kho tvaṃ, bhikkhu, attānaṃ kaṭuviyamakāsi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.128:4.2"
msgid "Taṃ vata bhikkhu kaṭuviyakataṃ attānaṃ āmagandhena avassutaṃ makkhikā nānupatissanti nānvāssavissantīti, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.128:4.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, so bhikkhu mayā iminā ovādena ovadito saṃvegamāpādī”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.128:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, one of the mendicants asked the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.128:4.5"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho, bhante, kaṭuviyaṃ? "
msgstr "“Sir, what is this ‘bitterness’? "

msgctxt "an3.128:4.6"
msgid "Ko āmagandho? "
msgstr "What is the ‘stench of rotting flesh’? "

msgctxt "an3.128:4.7"
msgid "Kā makkhikā”ti? "
msgstr "And what are the ‘flies’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.128:5.1"
msgid "“Abhijjhā kho, bhikkhu, kaṭuviyaṃ; "
msgstr "“Desire is bitterness; "

msgctxt "an3.128:5.2"
msgid "byāpādo āmagandho; "
msgstr "ill will is the stench of rotting flesh; "

msgctxt "an3.128:5.3"
msgid "pāpakā akusalā vitakkā makkhikā. "
msgstr "and bad, unskillful thoughts are the flies. "

msgctxt "an3.128:5.4"
msgid "Taṃ vata, bhikkhu, kaṭuviyakataṃ attānaṃ āmagandhena avassutaṃ makkhikā nānupatissanti nānvāssavissantīti, netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjatīti. "
msgstr "If you’re bitter, corrupted by the stench of rotting flesh, flies will, without a doubt, plague and infest you. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.281, sc6
msgctxt "an3.128:6.1"
msgid "Aguttaṃ cakkhusotasmiṃ, "
msgstr "When your eyes and ears are unguarded, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:6.2"
msgid "indriyesu asaṃvutaṃ; "
msgstr "and you’re not restrained in your sense faculties, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:6.3"
msgid "Makkhikānupatissanti, "
msgstr "flies—those lustful thoughts—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:6.4"
msgid "saṅkappā rāganissitā. "
msgstr "will plague you. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an3.128:7.1"
msgid "Kaṭuviyakato bhikkhu, "
msgstr "A mendicant who’s bitter, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:7.2"
msgid "āmagandhe avassuto; "
msgstr "corrupted by the stench of rotting flesh, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:7.3"
msgid "Ārakā hoti nibbānā, "
msgstr "is far from being extinguished, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:7.4"
msgid "vighātasseva bhāgavā. "
msgstr "anguish is their lot. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an3.128:8.1"
msgid "Gāme vā yadi vāraññe, "
msgstr "Whether in village or wilderness, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: samathamattano → samamattano (bj, s1-3, km) | sammamattano (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.128:8.2"
msgid "aladdhā samathamattano; "
msgstr "if they don’t find serenity in themselves, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Pareti → care (s1-3) | careti (mr)
msgctxt "an3.128:8.3"
msgid "Pareti bālo dummedho, "
msgstr "the fool, void of wisdom, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:8.4"
msgid "makkhikāhi purakkhato. "
msgstr "is honored only by flies. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "an3.128:9.1"
msgid "Ye ca sīlena sampannā, "
msgstr "But those who have ethics, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:9.2"
msgid "paññāyūpasameratā; "
msgstr "lovers of wisdom and peace, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:9.3"
msgid "Upasantā sukhaṃ senti, "
msgstr "they, being peaceful, sleep well, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.128:9.4"
msgid "nāsayitvāna makkhikā”ti. "
msgstr "since they’ve got rid of the flies.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.128:9.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
